success.question_text: What is the next number in this pattern?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Patterns
success.question_hint:
• Look at the gaps between the numbers.
  • Use the pattern of these numbers to find the next number.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

The differences between the numbers are 2, 4, 8 and 16.

The differences are doubling each time.

The next difference will be 2 × 16 = 32.

The next number will be 31 + 32 = 63.

Tip

Use the differences between successive terms in a pattern to give a hint as to the correct rule used in the pattern.

success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Simplifying
success.question_hint:
• (mn)3 means m3n3.
  • Look for what is common to both numerator and denominator and cancel.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

An index tells us the number of factors of a term that are multiplied together. For example, in this question there was one factor of m in the numerator and three factors of m in the denominator. After cancelling one factor of m, there are none left in the numerator and two factors of m left in the denominator. Similarly, three factors of n in the denominator cancel with three of the six in the numerator, leaving three factors of n in the numerator.
